Data Visualization Activity

#Calling my library
library (readr)
library (tidyverse)
##  Attaching packages  tidyverse 1.3.1 
##  ggplot2 3.3.5      dplyr   1.0.7
##  tibble  3.1.3      stringr 1.4.0
##  tidyr   1.1.4      forcats 0.5.1
##  purrr   0.3.4
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
## x dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
## x dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
library(ggplot2)
#Reading the data
url <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/fivethirtyeight/data/master/births/US_births_1994-2003_CDC_NCHS.csv"
cdcdata <- read_csv(url)
## Rows: 3652 Columns: 5
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## dbl (5): year, month, date_of_month, day_of_week, births
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
spec(cdcdata)
## cols(
##   year = col_double(),
##   month = col_double(),
##   date_of_month = col_double(),
##   day_of_week = col_double(),
##   births = col_double()
## )
#Using scatterplot to visualize my data
ggplot(data = cdcdata) +
  geom_point (mapping = aes (x = year, y = births, color = month))

#Using histogram to visualize my data
library (ggplot2)
ggplot(data = cdcdata) + 
  geom_histogram(mapping = aes(x = births), binwidth = 1000)
